BETABAR.information: Also known as "Choo Choo Water," nine out of ten scientists recommend trains drink at least half their body weight in fuel every day.
BETABAR.speechBubble: Don't drink fuel, it's not good for your bones.

RAD.information: The radiator uses air to cool various train parts. But this one seems like it can operate in outer space. We're not really sure how that works.
RAD.speechBubble: It's not a very good mattress...

RADFAN.information: The radiator fan pulls air into the radiator. Don't put your fingers too close to the spinning blades!
RADFAN.speechBubble: If you're not gonna use this, I know a guy in an office who may want it.

SANDBOX.information: Sand boxes drop sand on train tracks to improve wheel traction in slippery conditions. These ones also improve traction while traveling through wormholes.
SANDBOX.speechBubble: If you find any cereal on the tracks let me know. I want it back...

BATT.information: Trains use batteries to power electrical systems while the alternators are turned off. We guaruntee these ones won't lose their charge while traveling through time.
BATT.speechBubble: I, uh... What did you say? Everything is, like...really quiet.

FTANK.information: On a normal train, you have to refill your fuel tank frequently. But on a Century Train, the fuel tank fills itself.
FTANK.speechBubble: Stop asking me if I want coffee. I don't want it. It shrinks your boy parts.

AIRREZ.information: Air reservoirs hold the compressed air that operates your train's brakes. On a Century Train, the compressed air smells pine-fresh.
AIRREZ.speechBubble: Like, there's no way bees could fart that big... Right?

DRIVE.information: The drive shaft transports energy from the engine to other parts of the train. And this one manages to do it without energy loss!
DRIVE.speechBubble: Sorry I'm always wearing the same clothes. I haven't folded my laundry yet...in case I need a landing pad.

MOTBLOW.information: The motor blower provides air to the traction motors and alternators, keeping them cool during periods of heavy work. This one is very proud of its blowing skills.
MOTBLOW.speechBubble: Yeah I know my Oil Zone smells bad... Anyway, do you want some jellybeans?

ALTER.information: The main alternator receives power from the engine and converts it to alternating current, which powers the traction motors. On a Century Train, it also produces anomatter.
ALTER.speechBubble: Hey... Can you teach me how to buy milk?

WHEELS.information: Did you know wheels were invented by Thomas J. Wheel? It's true! Or, at least, these wheels were...
WHEELS.speechBubble: Oh, man, of all the wheels I've seen... Those are some of 'em.

ELECTRO.information: Electronic controls manage nearly every part of modern locomotives. On a Century Train, they also display information about atmospheric anomatter density.
ELECTRO.speechBubble: Did you hear about that weird thing in T-Pines where that deer kept pooping and then, like... Un-pooping?

TRUCK.information: The truck frame, or locomotive frame, is the backbone onto which the other train parts are mounted. It's like your train's skeleton. Spooky!
TRUCK.speechBubble: If you don't want it, I kinda wanna try to use it in another mattress race...

TRACMO.information: Traction motors receive energy from the main alternator, propelling the train forward. These ones are calibrated to travel forward, backward, and sideways through time.
TRACMO.speechBubble: I took a nap and when I woke up there were squirrels pinning me to the ground. Like, a hundred of them...

AUXALT.information: The auxiliary alternator sends electricity to rail cars and passenger cars. It makes sure your passengers and cargo are comfortable while traveling through space-time.
AUXALT.speechBubble: Okay, it started playing Imagine Dragons and I can't get it to stop. Can you please buy this thing?

AIRCOMP.information: The air compressor ensures that your train's ventillation and vacuum breaking systems function properly. On a Century Train, it also compresses anomatter to create time dilations and wormholes.
AIRCOMP.speechBubble: Don't breathe in soup man, it's not worth it. My lungs still feel spicy.

TURBO.information: The turbo charger pumps extra air into the engine's cylinders, resulting in higher fuel consumption and a boost in speed. This baby will get your Century Train from 0 to 88 in 2.5 seconds.
TURBO.speechBubble: Hey, if you see my turtle, can you tell him to come home? It's movie night and we're watching Herbie Fully Loaded...

POWER.information: The power rectifier converts alternating current into direct current. Most Modern Era trains don't need this part, but Century Trains require technology from the past, present, and future to time travel effectively.
POWER.speechBubble: Be careful with this thing, man. It made me start talking backwards when I slapped my butt cheeks, too.

ENGINE.information: The engine is the heart of the locomotive. You feed it fuel, and it pumps out energy. Century Train engines simultaneous exist on infinite planes of space-time, resulting in infinite energy generation.
ENGINE.speechBubble: I tried to stop aging when I hit, like, maximum DILF-iness. Do... Do you think it worked?
